{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐπιτήδ-ειος</b>, α, ον: <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>ἐπιτήδ-εος</b>, έη, εον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.158, +others (compare ἐπιταδεοτρώκτας)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>Doric dialect</i> <b>-τάδειος</b> [ᾱ] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 524.36 (Praesus, 3rd c.BC): regular _comparative_ and _superlative_ -ειότερος, -ειότατος, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.54, 7.86, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; -έστερος, -έστατος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anonymus cited in 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus see entry , 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 121: _Ionic dialect_ -εότερος, -εότατος, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.2, 1.110, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: (ἐπιτηδές):— <b>made for an end</b> or <b>purpose, fit</b> or <b>adapted for</b> <b>it, suitable, convenient,</b> νομαί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. passage], etc.:—Constr.: ἐ. ἔς τι [prev. work] 115 (_superlative_)\">Refs</a>], etc.; πρός τι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 390b: with \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, χωρίον -ότατον ἐνιππεῦσαι <b>most fit</b> to ride in, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.102, compare 9.2 (_comparative_), 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.20, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 1228, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 508; ἄνδρα -ότατον..δέξαι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.134, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 79; so ἐ. τῷ σώματι κινδυνεύειν 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 5.63 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. ὑπεξαιρεθῆναι <b>convenient</b> to be put out of the way, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.70; τεθνάναι μᾶλλον ἢ σῴζεσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.25, compare 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 30.24 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. ξυνεῖναι a <b>fit</b> person to live with, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 206 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also ἐ. ὀστρακισθῆναι <b>deserving</b> to be ostracized, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.36; ἐ. πάσχειν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 22.57 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκλεγόμενος τὸν ἐ. ἔπαισεν ἄν struck <b>him who deserved it,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.3.11 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but ἐ. ἐς ὀλιγαρχίαν ἐλθεῖν <b>likely</b> or <b>inclined</b> to come, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.63; also ὑμῖν ἐπιτήδεόν [ἐστι] οἰκέειν 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.158, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>useful, serviceable, necessary,</b> <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> of things, ὀλιγαρχία ἐ. τοῖς Λακεδαιμονίοις <b>fit</b> or <b>serviceable for..,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.81; ἐ. τῷ δήμῳ πράττειν 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 13.51 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; καταστήσειν ἐς τὸ ἐ. to their <b>advantage,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.76 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐδὲν ηὕροντο ἐ. no <b>advantage,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.58; οὐκ ἐ. καταγνῶναί τινος 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.97 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἱερὰ οὐκ ἐ., opposed to καλά, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 9.37: especially as \">Refs</a>] <i>substantive</i>, τὰ ἐ. things <b>requisite, necessaries,</b> especially of <b>provisions,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.174, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.23, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 2.2.2, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: also in <i>singular</i>, <b>what is requisite, needful,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Vect.” 4.38. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Leve